President Trump held a press conference at Camp David where he discussed various topics, including security, infrastructure, military funding, and the drug problem in the country. He also mentioned the possibility of working with Democrats on DACA and expressed his support for bipartisan cooperation in the coming year. The President also addressed issues related to North Korea, the Russia investigation, welfare reform, and immigration. He expressed his desire for a wall and increased border security, as well as the need to end chain migration and the visa lottery system. Trump also stated that he believes Mexico will eventually pay for the wall.